          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_1777782706:9c04462dadf6",
            "label": "Program Summary & Impact\n(Please limit to 200 words)",
            "help_text": "Briefly describe the program and the expected impact of the requested funding.",
            "field_type": "text",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "The Science Mission Directorate (SMD) conducts scientific exploration enabled by access to space. This $9 billion request supports missions across Earth Science, Planetary Science, Astrophysics, and Heliophysics. SMD investment drives American leadership in space, ensuring the U.S. remains the global partner of choice as international competition, particularly from China, accelerates. Locally, SMD funding supports critical innovation and workforce development in CA-40. In recent years, NASA has obligated over $1.1 million in the district. This includes significant grants to Chapman University for research in surface biology, ocean salinity monitoring, and environmental justice. Additionally, local contractors like Suss Microtec Inc and Paydarfar Industries, Inc. provide specialized equipment and services. This funding provides the stability necessary to maintain the highly skilled aerospace workforce and inspires the next generation of STEM professionals. By adhering to the peer-reviewed National Academies Decadal Surveys, SMD ensures that federal investments yield transformative discoveries and maintain our national prestige.",
            "rationale": "Combines the $9 billion request with local district spending data (Chapman University, Suss Microtec Inc) and strategic talking points regarding China and workforce stability.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_2051238938:bc26171b0f6b",
            "label": "Additional Background Information \n(If applicable, please limit to 500 words)",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* $1.15M in recent NASA Science obligations in CA-40; supports Chapman University ($1.17M cumulative grants) and high-tech contractors like Suss Microtec Inc ($1.08M cumulative contracts).\n* $9B request provides critical 24% increase over FY2026 enacted levels to restore mission stability and protect the specialized aerospace workforce and industrial base.\n* Strategic necessity to counter China's rapid space science expansion; ensures the U.S. continues to set international norms for 21st-century exploration and discovery.\n* High-ROI public investment returning $3 for every $1 spent; fuels CA-40 innovation economy and STEM pipeline through firms like Paydarfar Industries and Chroma Systems Solutions.",
            "rationale": "Drafted using specific CA-40 spending data ($1.15M total, Chapman University and Suss Microtec recipients) and strategic talking points regarding U.S. leadership, the $9B funding target, and economic impact.",
